00:39:26.540 --> 00:39:30.160
And bang, like you say,
they were quite clearly

00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:32.030
heavily pressured.

00:39:32.030 --> 00:39:36.010
But I think-- I've got
this great favorite passage

00:39:36.010 --> 00:39:40.465
from Hilary Mantel's "Wolf Hall"
where you remember, those you

00:39:40.465 --> 00:39:43.230
who've seen it, where Mark
Rylance, the kind of Thomas

00:39:43.230 --> 00:39:47.870
Cromwell figure, he gets this
hapless aristocrat called Harry

00:39:47.870 --> 00:39:49.070
Percy.

00:39:49.070 --> 00:39:50.570
And he's basically [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:50.570 --> 00:39:51.320
And he says, look.

00:39:51.320 --> 00:39:56.300
You think-- you think-- this is
in 1515, whatever-- you think

00:39:56.300 --> 00:40:01.270
the world is based on jousting
and castles and chivalry

00:40:01.270 --> 00:40:02.770
and feasts.

00:40:02.770 --> 00:40:04.757
I know the world is
based on banking.

00:40:04.757 --> 00:40:06.590
And I can switch-- I
know this because I can

00:40:06.590 --> 00:40:08.625
switch your world off tomorrow.

00:40:08.625 --> 00:40:09.730
I don't like you.

00:40:09.730 --> 00:40:10.690
I can take you out.

00:40:10.690 --> 00:40:12.910
You can't take me out.

00:40:12.910 --> 00:40:16.090
Postcapitalism is about
saying, look-- to capitalists--

00:40:16.090 --> 00:40:17.811
you think the world
is based on banking.

00:40:17.811 --> 00:40:19.810
You think the world is
based on private property

00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:21.680
and large monopolies, tech IP.

00:40:21.680 --> 00:40:23.600
We can switch it off.

00:40:23.600 --> 00:40:26.530
But I don't want to do it
in a kind of aggressive way.

00:40:26.530 --> 00:40:29.450
I want to persuade people that
we should switch part of it

00:40:29.450 --> 00:40:29.990
off.

00:40:29.990 --> 00:40:32.010
And yes, exactly
to create a bubble.

00:40:32.010 --> 00:40:35.326
And some of these bubbles are
not-- they're not smashable.

00:40:35.326 --> 00:40:38.220
A lot of the anarchist networks
in Athens have this slogan.

00:40:38.220 --> 00:40:40.120
You can't default on a squat.

00:40:40.120 --> 00:40:42.870
You can't default
on unoccupied space.

00:40:42.870 --> 00:40:45.570
I don't necessarily
think occupied spaces are

00:40:45.570 --> 00:40:48.160
the same as Wikipedia
or Ruby on Rails,

00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:49.870
whatever, open source projects.

00:40:49.870 --> 00:40:53.120
They're different parts of
what the world used to make,

00:40:53.120 --> 00:40:56.405
this synthetic, new
part of the economy.

00:40:56.405 --> 00:40:57.530
And we haven't done it yet.

00:40:57.530 --> 00:40:59.090
So I don't know.

00:40:59.090 --> 00:41:01.772
The transition is a challenge.

00:41:01.772 --> 00:41:04.607
AUDIENCE: How do you reconcile
that with [INAUDIBLE]?

00:41:04.607 --> 00:41:06.440
