no matter how long they spent

00:46:48.600 --> 00:46:51.760
in a lab and how boring it was,
this has to be deployed now.

00:46:51.760 --> 00:46:54.180
So we're going to
produce it generically.

00:46:54.180 --> 00:46:56.660
And the pharma industry has
had to react to that, probably

00:46:56.660 --> 00:46:59.545
not in a very-- in some sense,
not in a very virtuous way.

00:46:59.545 --> 00:47:00.920
Because what
they've had to do is

00:47:00.920 --> 00:47:05.740
pursue that form of intellectual
property, which is niche.

00:47:05.740 --> 00:47:07.495
So often, you get
pharmaceutical giants

00:47:07.495 --> 00:47:09.830
now looking for a
pipeline of products

00:47:09.830 --> 00:47:12.230
that is so niche that
you're sometimes wondering

00:47:12.230 --> 00:47:14.230
whether or not it's
simply designed to avoid

00:47:14.230 --> 00:47:15.688
the generic drug thing.

00:47:15.688 --> 00:47:17.104
AUDIENCE: No, I
think the way they

